07, \"text\": \"Christianity\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/History_of_Christianity\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/History_of_Christianity\"}, {\"begin\": 271, \"end\": 277, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Islam\", \"score\": 0.9964997427735707, \"rank\": 0.0035125520620956046, \"text\": \"Muslim\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Islam\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Islam\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The bishop\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 10}, {\"ngram\": \"the theatrical opening\", \"from\": 100, \"to\": 122}, {\"ngram\": \"the 2024 Summer Olympics\", \"from\": 126, \"to\": 150}, {\"ngram\": \"the Last Supper\", \"from\": 189, \"to\": 204}, {\"ngram\": \"the Olympic organizers\", \"from\": 219, \"to\": 241}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"A question I would pose--we all know the answer to it: 'Would they ever have dared mock Islam in a similar way?'\\\"\", \"from\": 286, \"to\": 400, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the answer\", \"from\": 324, \"to\": 334}, {\"ngram\": \"Islam\", \"from\": 375, \"to\": 380}, {\"ngram\": \"a similar way\", \"from\": 384, \"to\": 397}]}, {\"sentence\": \"asked Bishop Robert E. Barron, who is also the founder of the \\\"Word on Fire\\\" ministry, in an X-post.\", \"from\": 401, \"to\": 501, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 407, \"end\": 413, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bishop\", \"score\": 0.9989244999738082, \"rank\": 0.0010766579719882431, \"text\": \"Bishop\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bishop\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bishop\"}, {\"begin\": 424, \"end\": 430, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Family_of_Donald_Trump\", \"score\": 0.9999992229039272, \"rank\": 7.770965512917363e-07, \"text\": \"Barron\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Family_of_Donald_Trump\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Family_of_Donald_Trump\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the founder\", \"from\": 444, \"to\": 455}, {\"ngram\": \"Fire\", \"from\": 472, \"to\": 476}, {\"ngram\": \"an X\", \"from\": 491, \"to\": 495}, {\"ngram\": \"post\", \"from\": 496, \"to\": 500}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Barronsaid the enemies of Christianity are putting Christians on notice that the struggle is being fought right now: Friends, my thoughts on the opening ceremony of the Paris Olympics.#Olimpiadas2024#OlympicGamespic.twitter.com/xU1ljFMZft \\\"We should believe them,\\\" he said.\", \"from\": 503, \"to\": 778, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 529, \"end\": 541, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/History_of_Christianity\", \"score\": 0.8820840402119621, \"rank\": 0.13367882697192307, \"text\": \"Christianity\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/History_of_Christianity\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/History_of_Christianity\"}, {\"begin\": 554, \"end\": 564, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/History_of_Christianity\", \"score\": 0.9854952444929043, \"rank\": 0.01469468445682656, \"text\": \"Christians\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/History_of_Christianity\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/History_of_Christianity\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the enemies\", \"from\": 514, \"to\": 525}, {\"ngram\": \"notice\", \"from\": 568, \"to\": 574}, {\"ngram\": \"the struggle\", \"from\": 580, \"to\": 592}, {\"ngram\": \"Friends\", \"from\": 620, \"to\": 627}, {\"ngram\": \"my thoughts\", \"from\": 629, \"to\": 640}, {\"ngram\": \"the opening ceremony\", \"from\": 644, \"to\": 664}, {\"ngram\": \"Olympics.#Olimpiadas2024#OlympicGamespic.twitter.com\", \"from\": 678, \"to\": 730}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"They are telling us who they are,\\\" he said.\", \"from\": 780, \"to\": 824, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"us\", \"from\": 798, \"to\": 800}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"We should believe them, but furthermore, we Christians--we Catholics--should not be sheepish.\", \"from\": 825, \"to\": 919, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 870, \"end\": 880, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/History_of_Christianity\", \"score\": 0.9854952444929043, \"rank\": 0.01469468445682656, \"text\": \"Christians\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/History_of_Christianity\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/History_of_Christianity\"}, {\"begin\": 885, \"end\": 894, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Catholic_Church\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 9.587636946281938e-18, \"text\": \"Catholics\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Catholic_Church\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Catholic_Church\"}], \"noun_phrases\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"We should resist.\", \"from\": 920, \"to\": 937, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"We should make our voices heard.\\\"\", \"from\": 938, \"to\": 971, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"our voices\", \"from\": 953, \"to\": 963}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The opening ceremony for every Olympiad is always an opportunity for the host country to present its culture to a worldwide audience that could be in the billions.\", \"from\": 973, \"to\": 1136, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The opening ceremony\", \"from\": 973, \"to\": 993}, {\"ngram\": \"every Olympiad\", \"from\": 998, \"to\": 1012}, {\"ngram\": \"an opportunity\", \"from\": 1023, \"to\": 1037}, {\"ngram\": \"the host country\", \"from\": 1042, \"to\": 1058}, {\"ngram\": \"its culture\", \"from\": 1070, \"to\": 1081}, {\"ngram\": \"a worldwide audience\", \"from\": 1085, \"to\": 1105}, {\"ngram\": \"the billions\", \"from\": 1123, \"to\": 1135}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Friday's spectacular marked the first time that the opening ceremony was not contained in the main Olympic stadium.\", \"from\": 1138, \"to\": 1253, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the first time\", \"from\": 1166, \"to\": 1180}, {\"ngram\": \"the opening ceremony\", \"from\": 1186, \"to\": 1206}, {\"ngram\": \"the main Olympic stadium\", \"from\": 1228, \"to\": 1252}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Instead, the organizers also staged performances all over Paris by Beyonce, Celine Dion, and Lady Gaga, complemented by gymnasts on rooftops and a mysterious masked man character in 18th-century costume running through the city with the Olympic torch.\", \"from\": 1254, \"to\": 1505, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1312, \"end\": 1317, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.999999999998181, \"rank\": 1.6471580552637696e-12, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 1321, \"end\": 1328, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Beyonc\\u00e9\", \"score\": 0.999382060925257, \"rank\": 0.0005288616608031146, \"text\": \"Beyonce\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Beyonc\\u00e9\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Beyonc\\u00e9\"}, {\"begin\": 1330, \"end\": 1341, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Celine_Dion\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.73711284459051e-43, \"text\": \"Celine Dion\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Celine_Dion\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Celine_Dion\"}, {\"begin\": 1347, \"end\": 1356, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lady_Gaga\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Lady Gaga\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lady_Gaga\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lady_Gaga\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the organizers\", \"from\": 1263, \"to\": 1277}, {\"ngram\": \"performances\", \"from\": 1290, \"to\": 1302}, {\"ngram\": \"gymnasts\", \"from\": 1374, \"to\": 1382}, {\"ngram\": \"rooftops\", \"from\": 1386, \"to\": 1394}, {\"ngram\": \"a mysterious masked man character\", \"from\": 1399, \"to\": 1432}, {\"ngram\": \"18th-century costume\", \"from\": 1436, \"to\": 1456}, {\"ngram\": \"the city\", \"from\": 1473, \"to\": 1481}, {\"ngram\": \"the Olympic torch\", \"from\": 1487, \"to\": 1504}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Throughout the city, the French erected statues honoring the 10 golden heroines of French history: Olympe de Gouges, Alice Milliat, Gis\\u00e8le Halimi, Simone de Beauvoir, Paulette Nardal, Jeanne Barret, Louise Michel, Christine de Pizan, Alice Guy and Simone Veil.\", \"from\": 1507, \"to\": 1767, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1590, \"end\": 1604, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/History_of_France\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"French history\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/History_of_France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/History_of_France\"}, {\"begin\": 1606, \"end\": 1622, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympe_de_Gouges\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Olympe de Gouges\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympe_de_Gouges\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympe_de_Gouges\"}, {\"begin\": 1624, \"end\": 1637, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alice_Milliat\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Alice Milliat\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q36180\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alice_Milliat\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alice_Milliat\"}, {\"begin\": 1639, \"end\": 1652, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gis\\u00e8le_Halimi\", \"score\": 0.9999999984474925, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Gis\\u00e8le Halimi\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gis\\u00e8le_Halimi\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gis\\u00e8le_Halimi\"}, {\"begin\": 165