\"to\": 1766}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Somehow,St.\", \"from\": 1769, \"to\": 1780, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Somehow,St.\", \"from\": 1769, \"to\": 1780}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Joan of Arc, did not make the cut.\", \"from\": 1781, \"to\": 1815, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Joan\", \"from\": 1781, \"to\": 1785}, {\"ngram\": \"Arc\", \"from\": 1789, \"to\": 1792}, {\"ngram\": \"the cut\", \"from\": 1807, \"to\": 1814}]}, {\"sentence\": \"There was also a singing and dancing drag queen segment, which seemed connected to the drag staging of Leonardo da Vinci's \\\"Last Supper\\\" painting.\", \"from\": 1817, \"to\": 1963, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1920, \"end\": 1937, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Leonardo_da_Vinci\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.6781351038430115e-28, \"text\": \"Leonardo da Vinci\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Leonardo_da_Vinci\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Leonardo_da_Vinci\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a singing and dancing drag queen segment\", \"from\": 1832, \"to\": 1872}, {\"ngram\": \"the drag staging\", \"from\": 1900, \"to\": 1916}]}, {\"sentence\": \"This staging culminated in the drag personification of the Greek god of wine, feasting, and frivolity, Dionysus.\", \"from\": 1964, \"to\": 2076, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2023, \"end\": 2028, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Greek_mythology\", \"score\": 0.8549379756448348, \"rank\": 0.169115053575255, \"text\": \"Greek\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Greek_mythology\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Greek_mythology\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"This staging\", \"from\": 1964, \"to\": 1976}, {\"ngram\": \"the drag personification\", \"from\": 1991, \"to\": 2015}, {\"ngram\": \"wine\", \"from\": 2036, \"to\": 2040}, {\"ngram\": \"feasting\", \"from\": 2042, \"to\": 2050}, {\"ngram\": \"frivolity\", \"from\": 2056, \"to\": 2065}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The interpretation of the Greek God Dionysus makes us aware of the absurdity of violence between human beings.#Paris2024#OpeningCeremonypic.twitter.com/FBlQNNUmvV One easy interpretation of that juxtaposition is that the organizers were mocking the commemoration of Jesus Christ introducing to the Apostles the transubstantiation of the bread and wine at the table into the body and blood of Christ, which Catholics celebration in the Mass, with a rival deity with an alternative take on wine.\", \"from\": 2078, \"to\": 2572, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2104, \"end\": 2109, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Greek_mythology\", \"score\": 0.8549379756448348, \"rank\": 0.169115053575255, \"text\": \"Greek\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Greek_mythology\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Greek_mythology\"}, {\"begin\": 2114, \"end\": 2122, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dionysius_of_Halicarnassus\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.089518158174885e-27, \"text\": \"Dionysus\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dionysius_of_Halicarnassus\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dionysius_of_Halicarnassus\"}, {\"begin\": 2345, \"end\": 2357, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jesus\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.260150462925818e-13, \"text\": \"Jesus Christ\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jesus\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jesus\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The interpretation\", \"from\": 2078, \"to\": 2096}, {\"ngram\": \"us\", \"from\": 2129, \"to\": 2131}, {\"ngram\": \"the absurdity\", \"from\": 2141, \"to\": 2154}, {\"ngram\": \"violence\", \"from\": 2158, \"to\": 2166}, {\"ngram\": \"human beings.#Paris2024#OpeningCeremonypic.twitter.com/FBlQNNUmvV\", \"from\": 2175, \"to\": 2240}, {\"ngram\": \"One easy interpretation\", \"from\": 2241, \"to\": 2264}